    answer: "Dojo management software is a specialized platform for traditional martial arts schools. It handles student databases, kyu/dan rank tracking, grading ceremonies, class scheduling, and billing while using terminology and workflows appropriate to the dojo environment rather than generic gym language. Software tracks progression through belt systems, manages testing eligibility, maintains curriculum records, and supports family account relationships common in traditional training environments.",
    links: [
      { text: 'View all features', url: '/martial-arts-software/' },
      { text: 'See pricing', url: '/pricing/' }
    ]
  },
  {
    question: "How is dojo software different from gym software?",
    answer: "Dojo software is purpose-built for martial arts operations. It includes belt rank progression tracking, testing eligibility automation, curriculum management, and grading ceremony coordination—features absent from generic gym platforms. It also uses appropriate terminology (students vs members, dojo vs facility, sensei vs trainer, gi vs uniform) and understands cultural protocols like hierarchical student-teacher relationships, ceremonial aspects of testing, and multi-year developmental timelines.",
    links: [
      { text: 'Dojo vs gym software', url: '/martial-arts-software/' },
      { text: 'Karate-specific features', url: '/karate-school-software/' }
    ]
  },
